    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-02-04T04:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-02-04T04:30:00-05:00" n="417"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d417">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Conference files, lot 60 D 627, CF 192</note>
                <head>No. 417<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minutes of a Meeting of the Tripartite Working Group, Berlin,
                        February 4, 1954, 10:30 a.m.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/> BER MIN–11</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Berlin</placeName>, <date
                            ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-head" calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1954-02-04T10:30:00+01:00">February 4, 1954, 10:30 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="participants">
                    <item>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Present</hi>
                        <list>
                            <item>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">United States</hi>
                                <list>
                                    <item>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_MDII1">MacArthur</persName>
                                    </item>
                                </list>
                            </item>
                            <item>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">United Kingdom</hi>
                                <list>
                                    <item>
                                        <persName corresp="#p_RFK1">Sir Frank Roberts</persName>
                                    </item>
                                </list>
                            </item>
                            <item>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">France</hi>
                                <list>
                                    <item>M. <persName corresp="#p_SDCF1">Seydoux</persName>
                                    </item>
                                </list>
                            </item>
                        </list>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="italic">Tactics for Today</hi>. (a) It was agreed that M.
                                <persName corresp="#p_BGP1">Bidault</persName> would be asked by the
                            Chairman, Mr. <persName corresp="#p_EASA1">Eden</persName>, to speak
                            first. It was suggested that M. <persName corresp="#p_BGP1"
                                >Bidault</persName> begin by stating the fundamental importance of
                            the principle of free elections, then a brief, definitive statement on
                            the Bonn–Paris agreements, and close with further remarks on free
                            elections.</p>
                        <p>(b) Mr. <persName corresp="#p_EASA1">Eden</persName> would ask Mr.
                                <persName corresp="#p_MVM1">Molotov</persName> for his comments on
                            free elections.</p>
                        <p>(c) If Mr. <persName corresp="#p_MVM1">Molotov</persName> tables a
                            proposal, Mr. <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">Dulles</persName> might
                            suggest that the meeting adjourn for fifteen minutes for consideration
                            of the proposal. Mr. <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">Dulles</persName> will
                            then make preliminary comments on Mr. <persName corresp="#p_MVM1"
                                >Molotov</persName>’s proposal. If Mr. <persName corresp="#p_MVM1"
                                >Molotov</persName> raises again the question of an all-German
                            referendum, Mr. <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">Dulles</persName> will carry
                            the burden of argument.</p>
                        <p>(d) On the second round it was suggested that M. <persName
                                corresp="#p_BGP1">Bidault</persName> and Mr. <persName
                                corresp="#p_EASA1">Eden</persName> would continue to comment on free
                            elections. Mr. <persName corresp="#p_EASA1">Eden</persName> would prod
                            Mr. <persName corresp="#p_MVM1">Molotov</persName> to answer questions
                            on the UK Plan.<note n="1" xml:id="d417fn1">For the British plan, see
                                FPM(54)17, <ref target="#d510">Document 510</ref>.</note>
                        </p>
                    </item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>
                        <hi rend="italic">Possible Tripartite Document on Bonn-Paris
                        Agreements</hi>. <persName corresp="#p_RFK1">Sir Frank</persName> suggested
                        that if it appeared that Mr. <persName corresp="#p_MVM1">Molotov</persName>
                        planned to continue discussion of the Bonn-Paris agreements it might be
                        desirable to consider tabling a document setting forth the western views on
                        this subject. Mr. <persName corresp="#p_MDII1">MacArthur</persName> reserved
                        the U.S. position but said if the British prepared a draft we would be glad
                        to consider it further.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>
                        <hi rend="italic">Restricted Session</hi>. <persName corresp="#p_RFK1">Sir
                            Frank</persName> said Mr. <persName corresp="#p_EASA1">Eden</persName>
                        wished to avoid the appearance that the three western powers were attempting
                        to delay the holding of a restricted session. Mr. <persName
                            corresp="#p_EASA1">Eden</persName> had stated his preference for holding
                        the restricted session on Saturday. The views of the other ministers will be
                        sought.</item>
                    <pb facs="0987" n="953" xml:id="pg_953"/>
                    <label>4.</label>
                    <item>
                        <hi rend="italic">Declaration of Intent</hi>. The Declaration of Intent<note
                            n="2" xml:id="d417fn2">For the Declaration of Intent, see BER D–4/4c,
                                <ref target="#d511">Document 511</ref>.</note> should be considered
                        again tomorrow in light of any proposal Mr. <persName corresp="#p_MVM1"
                            >Molotov</persName> might make today.</item>
                    <label>5.</label>
                    <item>
                        <hi rend="italic">Tripartite Ministerial Meeting</hi>. It was noted that the
                        three Ministers would meet tomorrow at 12:00 at Mr. <persName
                            corresp="#p_DJF1">Dulles</persName>’ residence.<note n="3"
                            xml:id="d417fn3">For a report on this meeting, see <gloss
                                target="#t_Dulte1">Dulte</gloss> 40, <ref target="#d425">Document
                                425</ref>.</note> The U.S. Delegation will prepare a resume of the
                        work in progress in the Working Group.</item>
                </list>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
